description: Here's a great looking and driving 1966 Ford Fairlane 500 convertible just in at Unique Specialty and Classics!  This car has been restored and finished off in 1971 Grabber Yellow paint and black interior.  The power plant has also been updated with a 1993 Mustang Cobra 5.0 engine running the stock Cobra cam. The engine's  been paired to a C6 transmission for smooth reliable shifting and a 2:73 ratio rear end finishes putting the power to the pavement. The majority of the receipts are dated over the past 10-12 years and show the car has been well taken care of.  This is definitely a fun car to drive and ready for the next owner to take over and provide a good home for this beautiful convertible.  Check over the pictures from top to bottom we're sure you'll agree this is a nice looking car.  Check out the video and listen to the nice throaty rumble and great sound provided by the 302.
